= Disbelief (Kufr)


*Definition*:

- Linguistically: Kufr means to cover or conceal.
- In Islām : It is the opposite of Islām.


== Types of Kufr (Disbelief):


There are two types: Major Kufr (Kufr Akbar) and Minor Kufr (Kufr Asghar).


== Major Kufr (Kufr Akbar)


   *Definition*: It is the denial of belief in Allāh and His messengers #salamTHEM — whether this is done through rejection, or simply by refusing to believe, even without outright denial.


   *Ruling*: It takes one out of the religion of Islām.

   *Major Kufr is of five Types:*

      1. *Disbelief of Denial:* 
      This is the disbelief through rejecting and denying the truth. 
      
      Evidence is the saying of Allāh:

      #quran-block[وَمَنۡ أَظۡلَمُ مِمَّنِ ٱفۡتَرَىٰ عَلَى ٱللَّهِ كَذِبًا أَوۡ كَذَّبَ بِٱلۡحَقِّ لَمَّا جَآءَهُۥٓۚ أَلَيۡسَ فِي جَهَنَّمَ مَثۡوٗى لِّلۡكَٰفِرِينَ ٦٨
][And who is more unjust than one who invents a lie about Allāh or denies the truth when it comes to him? Is there not in Hell a home for the disbelievers? (Al-‘Ankabūt Q29:68)]
      
       

      2. *Disbelief of Pride and Arrogance Despite Belief:*

   This is when someone knows the truth, believes it inwardly, but refuses to accept it out of arrogance. 
   
   Evidence is the saying of Allāh:
   
   #quran-block[وَإِذۡ قُلۡنَا لِلۡمَلَٰٓئِكَةِ ٱسۡجُدُواْ لِأٓدَمَ فَسَجَدُوٓاْ إِلَّآ إِبۡلِيسَ أَبَىٰ وَٱسۡتَكۡبَرَ وَكَانَ مِنَ ٱلۡكَٰفِرِينَ ٣٤
][And [mention] when We said to the angels, ‘Prostrate to Ādam,’ and they prostrated, except for Iblis. He refused and was arrogant and became of the disbelievers. (Al-Baqarah Q2:34)]
   
    

   3. *Disbelief of doubt - Also Known as Disbelief of Suspicion:*
   

      This is when a person is unsure or doubts the truth, even if it has been made
      clear.
      
       Evidence is the saying of Allāh: #quran-block[وَدَخَلَ جَنَّتَهُۥ وَهُوَ ظَالِمٞ لِّنَفۡسِهِۦ قَالَ مَآ أَظُنُّ أَن تَبِيدَ هَٰذِهِۦٓ أَبَدٗا ٣٥
وَمَآ أَظُنُّ ٱلسَّاعَةَ قَآئِمَةٗ وَلَئِن رُّدِدتُّ إِلَىٰ رَبِّي لَأَجِدَنَّ خَيۡرٗا مِّنۡهَا مُنقَلَبٗا ٣٦
قَالَ لَهُۥ صَاحِبُهُۥ وَهُوَ يُحَاوِرُهُۥٓ أَكَفَرۡتَ بِٱلَّذِي خَلَقَكَ مِن تُرَابٖ ثُمَّ مِن نُّطۡفَةٖ ثُمَّ سَوَّىٰكَ رَجُلٗا ٣٧
لَّٰكِنَّا۠ هُوَ ٱللَّهُ رَبِّي وَلَآ أُشۡرِكُ بِرَبِّيٓ أَحَدٗا ٣٨
][He entered his garden while he was wronging
      himself. He said, ‘I do not think that this will perish – ever. And I do not
      think the Hour will occur. And even if I should be brought back to my Lord, I
      will surely find better than this as a return.’ His companion said to him while
      conversing, ‘Do you disbelieve in the One who created you from dust, then from a
      sperm-drop, and then fashioned you into a man? But as for me, He is Allāh, my
      Lord, and I do not associate anyone with my Lord.’ (Al-Kahf  Q18:35–38)]
       


   4. *Disbelief of Turning Away:*

      This is when a person completely ignores the truth, showing no concern to know
      it or act upon it. 
      
      Evidence is the saying of Allāh:
      
      #quran-block[مَا خَلَقۡنَا ٱلسَّمَٰوَٰتِ وَٱلۡأَرۡضَ وَمَا بَيۡنَهُمَآ إِلَّا بِٱلۡحَقِّ وَأَجَلٖ مُّسَمّٗىۚ وَٱلَّذِينَ كَفَرُواْ عَمَّآ أُنذِرُواْ مُعۡرِضُونَ ٣
][We did not create the heavens and earth and what is between them except in truth and [for] a specified term. But those who disbelieve, from that of which they are warned, are turning away. (Al-Aḥqāf Q46:3)]
      

   5. *Disbelief of Hypocrisy:*

      This refers to pretending to believe outwardly, while disbelieving inwardly.
      
      Evidence is the saying of Allāh:
      
      #quran-block[ذَٰلِكَ بِأَنَّهُمۡ ءَامَنُواْ ثُمَّ كَفَرُواْ فَطُبِعَ عَلَىٰ قُلُوبِهِمۡ فَهُمۡ لَا يَفۡقَهُونَ ٣
][That is because they believed, then they disbelieved; so
      their hearts were sealed, and they do not understand. (Al-Munāfiqūn
 Q63:3)]    
      
== Minor Kufr (Kufr Asghar)


*Definition*: It refers to any act of disobedience described in the Qurʾān
and Sunnah as Kufr, but which does not reach the level of major disbelief that
takes a person out of Islām.

*Its Ruling:*
 • It is forbidden and considered a major sin, but it does not take a person out of the fold of Islām.

*Examples of Minor Kufr:*
 1. Ingratitude for blessings:
 Allāh said:

#quran-block[وَضَرَبَ ٱللَّهُ مَثَلٗا قَرۡيَةٗ كَانَتۡ ءَامِنَةٗ مُّطۡمَئِنَّةٗ يَأۡتِيهَا رِزۡقُهَا رَغَدٗا مِّن كُلِّ مَكَانٖ فَكَفَرَتۡ بِأَنۡعُمِ ٱللَّهِ فَأَذَٰقَهَا ٱللَّهُ لِبَاسَ ٱلۡجُوعِ وَٱلۡخَوۡفِ بِمَا كَانُواْ يَصۡنَعُونَ ١١٢
][And Allah presents an example: a city which was safe and secure, its provision coming to it in abundance from every location, but it denied the favors of Allah. So Allah made it taste the envelopment of hunger and fear for what they had been doing. (An-Naḥl Q16:112)]



2. Fighting a fellow Muslim:
 
The Prophet #pbuh said:#hadith-block[سِبَابُ اَلْمُسْلِمِ فُسُوقٌ, وَقِتَالُهُ كُفْرٌ  مُتَّفَقٌ عَلَيْهِ.][Insulting a Muslim is wickedness, and fighting him is disbelief (kufr).
(Agreed upon)@muslim[vol. 1, p. 415, \#57]]


3. Mocking or attacking people’s lineage (ancestry):
 
The Prophet #pbuh said: #hadith-block[اثْنَتَانِ فِي النَّاسِ هُمَا بِهِمْ كُفْرٌ الطَّعْنُ فِي النَّسَبِ وَالنِّيَاحَةُ عَلَى الْمَيِّتِ][Two traits found among people are acts of kufr: attacking others’ lineage and wailing over the dead.
@muslim[vol. 1, p. 417, \#60]]


4. Wailing over the dead:
The Prophet #pbuh said:#hadith-block[اثْنَتَانِ فِي النَّاسِ هُمَا بِهِمْ كُفْرٌ الطَّعْنُ فِي النَّسَبِ وَالنِّيَاحَةُ عَلَى الْمَيِّتِ][Two traits found among people are acts of kufr: attacking others’ lineage and wailing over the dead.
@muslim[vol. 1, p. 417, \#60]]
